CatDescriptText: The Gaines Funeral Home, George W. Gaines proprietor, had opened at 220 Auburn Street in the East Liberty neighborhood by 1941.  The Gaines family lived on the premises at 220-224 Auburn.
TitMainTitle: Row of eight cars and hearses parked in front of Gaines Funeral Home with garage with Duquesne Baking Company sign in background, Auburn Street, East Liberty
